OL,3,CRobison urges UK Government to
OL,4,C'finally step up' and support Glasgow
OL,5,Cafter fire
OL,7,FLast week, Susan Aitken, the leader of
OL,8,FSNP-run Glasgow City Council, called
OL,9,Fon UK ministers to provide help,
OL,10,Fsaying they "absolutely have a role in
OL,11,Fthis and I would like to hear what
OL,12,Ftheir offer is".
OL,14,FGlasgow Central, Scotland's busiest
OL,15,Fstation, partially reopened on
OL,16,FWednesday, 10 days after the blaze
OL,17,Ftore through a neighbouring building.
OL,19,FDemolition work has now begun on the
OL,20,Fremains of the B-listed Victorian
OL,21,Fstructure.
OL,26,@rD@MOUtD@OO]
